        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 7:29PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 729 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Uptown Charlotte, or near Southpark Mall, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
East Charlotte, Matthews, Freedom Park, Southpark Mall, South
Charlotte, The Arboretum, and Central Charlotte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
